==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{SAMPA|/'traI.@mf/}}
===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From Latinised Greek [[triumphus]] (via earlier Etruscan [[triumpus]] ) "a triumph, a victory", from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[θρίαμβος]]''' (''thriambos'') "a hymn to Dionysos", also "an epithet of Dionysos", a refer to the merriment and rejoicing, for whatever reason.
===Noun===
'''triumph''' (''plural:'' [[triumphs]])

#Conclusive success following effort, conflict, or the confrontation of obstacles; victory; conquest; as, the triumph of knowledge.
#A magnificent and imposing ceremonial performed in honor of a victor who has prevailed decisively over an opponent.
#Hence, any triumphal procession; a pompous exhibition; a stately show or pageant.
#A state of joy or exultation at success.
#A trump card; also, a game at cards.

